  "beats": [
    {
      "text": "Part 2 of The Era of Substrates series. A Battlefield Without a Map.",
      "image": {
        "type": "slide",
        "slide": {
          "layout": "title",
          "title": "The Era of Substrates",
          "subtitle": "Part 2: A Battlefield Without a Map",
          "author": "@NuttyCLD",
          "note": "Semiconductor Packaging's Three-Way War"
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "text": "Glass substrates were supposed to be the inevitable next generation. But the reality is far more complex.",
      "image": {
        "type": "slide",
        "slide": {
          "layout": "bigQuote",
          "quote": "Glass substrates are the inevitable next generation after organic. Low CTE, superior signal integrity, panel-level scalability. It's only a matter of time before the technically superior material replaces the incumbent.",
          "author": "The Prevailing Assumption",
          "role": "Part 2 begins by questioning this very conviction."
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "text": "Three competing substrate technologies are battling for dominance: glass, organic, and silicon-based solutions.",
      "image": {
        "type": "slide",
        "slide": {
          "layout": "columns",
          "title": "Three Camps, One Battlefield",
          "subtitle": "Competing substrate technologies for next-gen AI chips",
          "columns": [
            {
              "title": "Glass",
              "accentColor": "primary",
              "icon": "🔷",
              "content": [
                { "type": "bullets", "items": ["Low CTE matching", "Superior signal integrity", "Panel-level scalability", "Economics gap still too wide"] }
              ]
            },
            {
              "title": "Organic",
              "accentColor": "success",
              "icon": "🟢",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "bullets",
                  "items": ["25 years of production infra", "ABF at 95%+ market share", "Sub-5μm race underway", "Has NOT hit physical wall"]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "title": "Silicon",
              "accentColor": "accent",
              "icon": "🟣",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "bullets",
                  "items": ["TSMC CoWoS dominance", "Chronic bottleneck = leverage", "CoPoS panel innovation", "CoWoP could kill substrates"]
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "text": "The glass camp has no clear leader despite massive investment.",
      "image": {
        "type": "slide",
        "slide": {
          "layout": "grid",
          "title": "[Glass] A Battlefield Without a Leader",
          "subtitle": "The armory is overflowing with weapons. But no leader has stepped forward.",
          "gridColumns": 3,
          "items": [
            {
              "title": "Intel",
              "accentColor": "primary",
              "icon": "🏭",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "bullets",
                  "items": [
                    "Decade of work, $1B+ invested",
                    "Holds ~50% of all patents",
                    "Key engineer Gang Duan left for Samsung",
                    "Flirting with IP licensing",
                    "Commercial production unlikely before 2030"
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "title": "Samsung",
              "accentColor": "info",
              "icon": "🔬",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "bullets",
                  "items": [
                    "Most ambitious vertical integration",
                    "SEMCO + Display + Foundry",
                    "Recruited Gang Duan from Intel",
                    "Prototypes failed customer specs (Nov 2025)",
                    "Infrastructure impressive, quality is not"
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "title": "Absolics (SKC)",
              "accentColor": "warning",
              "icon": "🏗️",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "bullets",
                  "items": [
                    "$600M factory in Georgia",
                    "$175M CHIPS Act support",
                    "Missing: a major customer",
                    "AMD closest but small volumes",
                    "Mass production slipped to 2027"
                  ]
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "text": "Old physics doesn't die easily. The organic camp is fighting back hard.",
      "image": {
        "type": "slide",
        "slide": {
          "layout": "split",
          "left": {
            "title": "[Organic] Old Physics Doesn't Die",
            "subtitle": "The incumbent fights back",
            "accentColor": "success",
            "dark": true,
            "ratio": 45,
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "callout",
                "text": "We underestimate iterative incremental gains on old physics and overestimate our ability to tame new physics for large volume manufacturing.",
                "label": "Raja Koduri",
                "style": "quote"
              }
            ]
          },
          "right": {
            "title": "Key Players",
            "content": [
              { "type": "text", "value": "Ajinomoto ABF", "bold": true, "color": "success" },
              {
                "type": "bullets",
                "items": [
                  "95%+ global market — de facto monopoly",
                  "Current: ~10μm L/S, leading edge: 5-7μm",
                  "Sub-5μm demos already on the table",
                  "50% capacity expansion by 2030"
                ]
              },
              { "type": "divider" },
              { "type": "text", "value": "Intel EMIB", "bold": true, "color": "primary" },
              {
                "type": "bullets",
                "items": ["Silicon bridges inside organic substrate", "Apple, Qualcomm, MediaTek eyeing it", "CoWoS bypass gaining traction"]
              },
              { "type": "divider" },
              { "type": "text", "value": "Chipletz", "bold": true, "color": "accent" },
              { "type": "bullets", "items": ["Smart Substrate — no silicon interposer", "SKC (Absolics parent) holds 12%"] }
            ]
          }
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "text": "TSMC controls the bottleneck — and that bottleneck is a weapon, not a weakness.",
      "image": {
        "type": "slide",
        "slide": {
          "layout": "columns",
          "title": "[Silicon] The One Who Grips the Bottleneck",
          "subtitle": "TSMC's CoWoS shortage paradoxically maximizes pricing power and locks mega-customers in place",
          "columns": [
            {
              "title": "Extension",
              "accentColor": "primary",
              "num": 1,
              "content": [
                { "type": "text", "value": "Scale CoWoS capacity", "bold": true },
                { "type": "bullets", "items": ["AP8 & Chiayi AP7 fabs", "60-70% output increase by end of 2026", "Most reliable, intuitive card"] }
              ]
            },
            {
              "title": "Transformation",
              "accentColor": "accent",
              "num": 2,
              "content": [
                { "type": "text", "value": "CoPoS — Panel-on-Substrate", "bold": true },
                {
                  "type": "bullets",
                  "items": ["310×310mm square panels", "VisEra pilot 2026, mass prod 2028", "NVIDIA as first customer", "Can absorb glass into TSMC ecosystem"]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "title": "Deconstruction",
              "accentColor": "danger",
              "num": 3,
              "content": [
                { "type": "text", "value": "CoWoP — Chip-on-Wafer-on-PCB", "bold": true },
                {
                  "type": "bullets",
                  "items": [
                    "Eliminates substrate layer entirely",
                    "Led by SPIL with NVIDIA",
                    "Enormous practical barriers",
                    "If it works: substrates cease to exist"
                  ]
                }
              ]
            }
          ],
          "showArrows": true,
          "callout": {
            "text": "TSMC has no reason to rush the resolution of this golden bottleneck.",
            "color": "warning"
          }
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "text": "Six critical signals will determine which way the fog clears.",
      "image": {
        "type": "slide",
        "slide": {
          "layout": "table",
          "title": "Signals to Read at the Crossroads",
          "subtitle": "The signal that converts to \"achieved\" first determines which way the fog clears",
          "headers": ["Camp", "Signal", "What It Means"],
          "rows": [
            [{ "text": "Glass", "color": "primary", "bold": true }, "Absolics's first PO (AMD)", "\"Experiment\" becomes \"industry\""],
            [{ "text": "Glass", "color": "primary", "bold": true }, "Samsung qualification gate", "Second player verified = real industry"],
            [{ "text": "Organic", "color": "success", "bold": true }, "ABF sub-5μm mass production", "Old guard holds; glass pushed to 2030s"],
            [{ "text": "Organic", "color": "success", "bold": true }, "Intel EMIB goes mainstream", "Organic-based approach handles next-gen"],
            [{ "text": "TSMC", "color": "accent", "bold": true }, "VisEra CoPoS panel pilot", "TSMC controls substrate choice"],
            [{ "text": "TSMC", "color": "accent", "bold": true }, "CoWoP feasibility proven", "\"Substrate\" category ceases to exist"]
          ],
          "rowHeaders": false,
          "striped": true
        }
      }
    },
    {
